<TITLE> Emergency must go before national polls: law adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 28 (bdnews24.com)Law adviser AF Hassan Ariff Thursday said the state of emergency must be lifted before national elections. Also, the emergency rule will be relaxed before elections to city corporations, Hassan Ariff, also land adviser, added in a weekly news briefing at the land ministry. "The state of emergency must be withdrawn before the national elections. Discussion on the issue is going on," he said. Answering another query he said: "Efforts are underway to amend the Contempt of Court Act." The government is proceeding carefully about the planned amendment as the adviser has said it does not want to be charged with "contempt of court in amending the law". Hassan Ariff said the law had been misused. Asked whether the law was being amended under pressure from civil servants, the adviser said: "It is not being done under any pressure." bdnews24.com/
